# This file documents the cross-workspace environment strategy for TimeLend.
# It exists to show where each module expects its own environment variables.
# It fits the system by keeping deployment and local setup predictable before full feature implementation.

# Frontend variables belong in frontend/.env.local or frontend/.env.example.
# Backend variables belong in backend/.env.example.
# Database variables belong in database/.env.example.
# Smart contract variables belong in smartContract/.env.example.
